title.narrative: 3.2 Health professionals and other relevant service providers have increased capacity to deliver quality comprehensive and systems- based health, nutrition and early childhood development services

description.narrative: Programme interventions have improved the capacities of health professionals and other ECD service providers to deliver quality health, nutrition and ECD services, evidenced through the successful roll out of the ECD model, and integration of child development and well-being into a holistic approach. With the timely provision of essential medical supplies, UNICEF contributed significantly to avoid adverse consequences in health care provision to vulnerable children and women resulting from the Great March of Return. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2020
